                            These diseases mostly occur due to aging and are progressive, however, there are treatments that can help with improving the patients quality of life.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <b>Epilepsy:</b> This disorder takes place due to the irregular electrical activity in the brain, which leads to seizures.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <b>Stroke:</b> This happens when the brain doesnt receive enough blood and nutrients, which can lead to severe brain damage.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <b>Parkinsons disease:</b> This is a neurological disease that affects the motor system of the human body and takes place due to the lack of dopamine-producing cells.
                            The patient can experience tremors and impaired coordination and balance.
                        </p>
